OL,4,Cabsences as part of attendance drive
OL,6,FGeoff Barton, general secretary of the
OL,7,FAssociation of School and College
OL,8,FLeaders (ASCL), said: "It is not
OL,9,Funreasonable to increase the level of
OL,10,Ffines for unauthorised absence given
OL,11,Fthat they have been fixed at #60 for
OL,12,Fseveral years.
OL,14,F"However, it is important to
OL,15,Funderstand that these fines
OL,16,Fpredominately relate to pupils who are
OL,17,Ftaken out of school for term-time
OL,18,Fholidays. While nobody wants to be in
OL,19,Fa position of fining parents there
OL,20,Fsimply has to be a marker that this is
OL,21,Fnot acceptable.
OL,26,@pD@WOUvD@AOU
